=====================================================================
VIII. GM NOTES & PACING
=====================================================================
- The parallel is the doc. Run their beats adjacent: when Hircine
  gifts Saijah, cut to Ylva's face. When Ylva transforms to solve a
  problem, let Saijah feel the argument it makes. Passive recruitment
  (ylva doc, Section VIII) is now active comparison.
- Do not force the crossroads. Fire B forces it only if the party
  climbs; if they choose another fire, the second approach still
  lands at the next dragon and the crossroads waits. The rebound
  binding (Section III) travels with the scene wherever it happens.
- Kynareth's break must be EARNED and environmental. No words. If
  the players miss the mercy trigger, the silence holds -- that is
  the goddess being exactly who she is.
- Hircine is never a villain in this. He is honest, patient, and he
  thinks he is giving each woman the truest gift in his power. The
  tragedy needs his sincerity.
- Ylva's rawness stays UNDER the boister. She is slightly less loud,
  never explained. If a player asks her directly, she tells the
  truth -- she has never once lied about anything that matters.
